US GOVERNMENT TELEPHONE INTERCEPT: From an Internet Café in Moscow to a pre-paid cell phone in Yemen, 4 February 2009.Translated from Russian, the receiver of the phone call is identified as Saleh Ahmed. The caller says, “Your brother Leonid is dead, but I will be like a brother to you.” The person receiving the call says in Russian, but with an Arabic accent, “I am truly blessed to know you, Mikhail Dombrovski.  I will need your support to continue to build the family farm. Shall we plan a family reunion?”  The caller says, “Soon, my brother, very soon.”